column5: looks like a great fish, Chad!!! Congratulation on your PB walleye/pickerel!  :clapping:
Congrats on a great fish. So your truck is a portable hut eh. Nice to see you remembered more the a handful is a waste and let that one go.

Thanks again all. My truck has been my best fishing buddy for the past two years.  During winter, I keep on average two under-slot fish per week which equals two walleye meals for the wife and I.  We need no more and wouldn't want any less.  Only one week left on Nipissing for this winter!
Nice eye!  TDunn
Only two fish caught tonight on Nipissing , which is really odd. Missed three big fish in a row, then finally landed this one. 8.5lbs on scale , estimating 27.5 to 28"
Nice fish!
Beauty!!
Nice pickereye!
Way to go Chad!  Congrats
Nice fish. We caught 6 this afternoon. My 2 keepers added up to 27.5".
Nice fish chad!!!
wicked nice fish RC! Congrats! Looks very fat too!
Great job Chad    Congrats on your PB     Nice junk of gold
Great stuff Chad !! Hoping I can find one next week... if I can get North that is....
:clapping: WTG!
Thats a beauty!! Do you fish from the cab of the truck with the extra reach of that pole?
thanks for the kudos guys!! I put her back down the hole to bite another minnow!
sometimes... it was very mild tonight, so I went free hand.
C'est beau !! Congrats
Awesome fish Chad! Congrats
VvEeRrYy NNNNIIIICCCCEEEE Tight Lines SBK
Sweet. And by hand. Good job
Nice Walter man !!!!!
Wow, nice one chad. No wonder nothing else was caught. That monster was scareing all the other fish away.
Nice pic, thanx for sharing.  Good on ya for the release.
Sweet catch man....

Actually caught it with the rod you see in the pic...just a small northland ice rod...it's sitting in my holder in the photo. Was using a Dartees spoon and minnow tipper.  I was thinking the same thing. When this girl bit, there must have been a school of big ones cruising around because I had three in a row slam my lure and I played them too quick and lost them, definitly wasn't the same fish everytime because I had them right up to the ice before they slipped off. I was sure it was a bunch of greasy ling haha.  Thanks! Anything over the slot goes back down the hole for me. My frying pan isn't big enough for such a big filet haha.
Great catch and congrats on the PB !!
